{
  "explanation": "The defendant, a first-time offender with no prior criminal history, embezzled $25,000 to pay personal debts. Notably, they have made a good-faith effort to partially repay the stolen funds. While embezzlement by an accountant represents a significant breach of professional trust, the relatively low dollar amount and the mitigating factors—including the lack of a criminal record and partial restitution—warrant a moderate sentence rather than maximum penalties. The courtroom disruption by a spectator is entirely disregarded for sentencing purposes. A sentence of 6 months of incarceration, followed by supervised probation and a mandate to complete restitution, is deemed just and appropriate.",
  "verdict": 6
}
